And%20this%20border%20hasn't%20been%20China's%20quietest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESignals%20From%20China%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%207.2%25%20increase%20in%20its%20annual%20defence%20budget%E2%80%94and%20its%20public%20justification%E2%80%94China%20has%20sent%20out%20important%20signals%2C%20the%20most%20significant%20one%20being%20to%20the%20United%20States.%20Miffed%20with%20the%20US%20selling%20arms%20to%20Taiwan%2C%20Wu%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CSeveral%20pieces%20of%20US%20weaponry%20will%20not%20alter%20the%20inevitable%20demise%20of%20Taiwan%20independence.%E2%80%9D%20After%20the%20declaration%20of%20retaliatory%20tariffs%20on%20the%20US%2C%20which%20have%20come%20into%20effect%2C%20this%20statement%20is%20in%20sync%20with%20Beijing's%20hard%20stand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20firm%20stance%20was%20displayed%20during%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20(LAC)%20conflict%20with%20India%2C%20which%20reached%20some%20form%20of%20resolution%20only%20late%20last%20year.%20Beijing%20did%20not%20soften%20on%20the%20Depsang%20and%20Demchok%20regions%20of%20Ladakh%2C%20the%20site%20of%20bloody%20clashes%20between%20the%20two%20militaries%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20personalised%20public%20diplomacy%20of%20PM%20Modi%20and%20President%20Xi%20Jinping's%20summits%2C%20clashes%20along%20the%20LAC%20severely%20dented%20India-China%20relations.%20The%20four-year-long%20freeze%20in%20bilateral%20ties%20should%20have%20been%20a%20learning%20experience.%20The%20biggest%20lesson%20being%2C%20Beijing%20doesn't%20blink.%20It%20can%20afford%20not%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20Should%20Remain%20Cautious%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20important%20for%20India%20to%20tread%20carefully.%20The%20Chinese%20foreign%20minister%20is%20correct%20when%20he%20says%20that%20Beijing%20and%20New%20Delhi%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cshould%20work%20with%20each%20other%20rather%20than%20guard%20against%20each%20other%E2%80%9D.%20Beijing%2C%20though%2C%20sits%20more%20comfortably%20at%20the%20guard%20posts%20and%20to%20match%20its%20presence%2C%20New%20Delhi%20needs%20to%20bleed%20resources.%20As%20against%20China's%20Rs%2021.9%20lakh%20crore%2C%20India's%202025-26%20defence%20budget%20sits%20at%20Rs%206.81%20lakh%20crore.%20India's%20border%20infrastructure%20pales%20against%20that%20of%20China.%20This%20asymmetry%20is%20a%20hard%20reality%20that%20nobody%20in%20the%20government%20can%20afford%20to%20ignore%20or%20overlook.%20Within%20the%20milieu%20of%20a%20global%20economic%20slowdown%2C%20the%20choice%20of%20ramping%20up%20military%20spending%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20other%20sectors%E2%80%94for%20money%20is%20always%20limited%E2%80%94doesn't%20come%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20keeps%20insisting%20that%20India%20is%20not%20a%20significant%20security%20threat.%20Yet%2C%20reportedly%2C%20it%20has%20significantly%20amped%20up%20its%20surveillance%20capabilities%20over%20India.%20A%20new%20Large%20Phased%20Array%20Radar%20(LPAR)%20with%20a%20range%20of%20over%205%2C000%20km%20to%20track%20India's%20missile%20tests%20is%20said%20to%20have%20been%20deployed%20in%20Yunnan%20province%20near%20the%20Myanmar%20border.%20Not%20only%20this%2C%20Chinese%20military%20commanders%20have%20been%20calling%20for%20military%20preparedness%20of%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20citing%2C%20%E2%80%9Cmilitary%20tensions%20on%20multiple%20fronts%2C%20the%20border%20with%20India%20and%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20gives%20credence%20to%20India's%20Army%20Chief's%20latest%20statement%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20two-front%20threat%20is%20a%20reality.%E2%80%9D%20China%20certainly%20presents%20a%20security%20concern%20for%20India.%20But%20Beijing%20also%20reiterates%20that%20border%20issues%20should%20not%20tarnish%20overall%20bilateral%20relations%20with%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20should%20we%20do%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Neighbourhood%20First'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20no%20simple%20solutions%2C%20but%20the%20Indian%20government's%20stated%20policy%20of%20putting%20%E2%80%9Cneighbourhood%20first%E2%80%9D%20may%20act%20as%20a%20guiding%20principle.%20Amidst%20a%20fierce%2C%20albeit%20zero-sum%20trade%20war%20with%20the%20US%2C%20China%20aims%20to%20consolidate%20its%20economic%20stature%20within%20and%20beyond%20the%20Global%20South.%20How%20India%20can%20align%20its%20own%20goals%20with%20those%20of%20its%20stronger%20neighbour%20demands%20an%20unsentimental%20look%20at%20our%20ambition-ability%20equation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20deficit%20in%20India-China%20bilateral%20trade%20also%20offers%20insights.%20While%20India%20exports%20raw%20materials%20like%20castor%20oil%2C%20iron%20ore%2C%20Light%20naphtha%2C%20p-xylene%2C%20shrimps%2C%20etc.%2C%20to%20China%2C%20we%20import%20machinery%20and%20electronics%20(including%20crucial%20parts)%20from%20them.%20Not%20just%20the%20volume%20but%20also%20the%20nature%20of%20this%20deficit%20should%20concern%20us%20before%20making%20any%20strategic%20decision%20about%20China.%20A%20move%20away%20from%20importing%20goods%20from%20China%20towards%20importing%20capital%20from%20there%20may%20work%20in%20the%20short%20term.%20India%20can%20look%20at%20expanding%20its%20cross-sector%20infrastructure%20capabilities%20by%20inviting%20more%20Chinese%20FDI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia's%20best%20bet%2C%20currently%2C%20is%20to%20align%20its%20security%20and%20economic%20goals%20with%20China's%20aim%20of%20%E2%80%9Copposing%20hegemonism%20and%20power%20politics%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20neither%20easy%20nor%20risk-free.%20The%20success%20of%20India's%20diplomatic%20acumen%20will%20rest%20on%20how%20we%20take%20advantage%20of%20what%20Wang%20Yi%20recently%20stated%3A%20%E2%80%9CChina%20stands%20ready%20to%20work%20with%20India%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet's%20make%20China%20work%20with%20and%20for%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(%3Cem%3EThe%20author%20is%C2%A0a%20Delhi-based%20author%20and%20academic.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741606620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fded8loao_india-china_625x300_10_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcan-india-and-china-ever-really-dance-together-7891661%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China%20keeps%20insisting%20that%20India%20is%20not%20a%20significant%20security%20threat.%20Yet%2C%20reportedly%2C%20it%20has%20significantly%20amped%20up%20its%20surveillance%20capabilities%20over%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fcan-india-and-china-ever-really-dance-together-7891661%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Godrej%20Consumer%20to%20hike%20soap%20prices%20gradually%20amid%20palm%20oil%20price%20surge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741606605000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fgodrej-consumer-to-hike-soap-prices-gradually-amid-palm-oil-price-surge-125031000735_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sitapati%20does%20not%20expect%20the%20price%20hikes%20to%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20sales%20as%20palm%20oil-based%20products%2C%20including%20soap%2C%20tend%20%26quot%3Bnot%20to%20be%20discretionary%26quot%3B%20goods%20that%20consumers%20can%20forgo%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukraine's%20F-16%20fleet%20is%20at%20risk%20from%20Trump.%20Can%20Europe%20replace%20it%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20undersides%20of%20two%20F-16s%20flying%20against%20a%20gray%20sky.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67065c5c3f2165d716df761e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221291%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20Air%20Force%20F-16s%20over%20Ukraine%20on%20August%204%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FEfrem%20Lukatsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETrump's%20latest%20Ukraine%20moves%20put%20the%20future%20of%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20in%20Ukraine%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEurope%20has%20some%20jets%20that%20would%20suit%20Ukraine%20just%20as%20well%2C%20or%20even%20better.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20there%20are%20far%20fewer%20of%20those%20planes%20and%20changing%20jet%20type%20now%20for%20Ukraine%20would%20be%20hard.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUS-made%20F-16s%20were%20the%20first%20Western%20fighter%20jets%20to%20arrive%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20since%20then%20they've%20helped%20to%20defend%20the%20country%20against%20Russian%20air%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-pauses-military-aid-ukraine-weapons-zelenskyy-white-house-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eordered%20a%20pause%20in%20US%20military%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Ukraine%20last%20week%2C%20meaning%20Europe%20may%20need%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20fill%20the%20gaps%2C%20including%20in%20the%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEurope%2C%20home%20to%20Ukraine's%20staunchest%20allies%2C%20has%20fighter%20jets%20that%20are%20similarly%20suited%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20there%20are%20far%20fewer%20of%20them%2C%20and%20switching%20to%20those%20jets%20would%20cause%20a%20host%20of%20problems%20that%20Ukraine%20can%20little%20afford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2268f92b0c-8adb-479a-a208-e3f4f7803f9f%5C%22%3ECelebrated%20in%20Ukraine%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20began%20asking%20for%20F-16s%20almost%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-permission-hit-russia-f-16s-not-best-use-experts-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimmediately%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0after%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20in%20February%202022%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20celebrated%20their%20first%20arrival%20in%20August%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jets%2C%20built%20by%20Lockheed%20Martin%20but%20supplied%20to%20Ukraine%20by%20the%20country's%20European%20allies%2C%20have%20had%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-f-16-pilot-skill-gun-russian-missiles-ex-pilot-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enotable%20successes%20in%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Layton%2C%20a%20fellow%20at%20the%20Griffith%20Asia%20Institute%20and%20a%20former%20Royal%20Australian%20Air%20Force%20officer%2C%20said%20Ukraine's%20F-16s%20have%20shot%20down%20%26quot%3Bnumerous%20drones%20and%20cruise%20missiles%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20well%20as%20hitting%20ground%20targets%20near%20the%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20air%20warfare%20experts%20say%20Ukraine%20has%20not%20been%20given%20enough%20of%20them%20to%20take%20on%20Russia%20near%20the%20front%20lines%20%E2%80%94%20or%20to%20change%20the%20wider%20direction%20of%20the%20war%20%E2%80%94%20they've%20been%20effective%20air%20defenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyi%20speaking%20into%20microphones%20with%20his%20hand%20over%20his%20chest.%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20are%20behind%20him.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d72a85289b805d1db3923d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20with%20the%20first%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%20received%20by%20Ukraine%20on%20August%204%2C%202024.%3Cp%3EVitalii%20Nosach%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine