r.com%2F67cb623b585f1dff88b18ef5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225369%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENick%20Allardice%20(not%20pictured)%2C%20his%20partner%2C%20and%20his%20friends%20bought%20a%20brownstone%20in%20Brooklyn%20together.%3Cp%3EIvan%20Pantic%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENick%20Allardice%2C%2038%2C%20lives%20in%20a%20brownstone%20in%20Brooklyn%20in%20an%20%26quot%3Bintentional%20community.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20and%20his%20partner%20bought%20the%20brownstone%20with%20three%20friends%20to%20reduce%20costs%20and%20create%20community.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20have%20family%20dinners%20on%20Sunday%20nights%20and%20regularly%20spend%20time%20together.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Nick%20Allardice.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20an%20unconventional%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20co-owned%20their%20large%20house%20in%20rural%20Australia%20with%20two%20other%20couples%20and%20their%20kids%2C%20forming%20an%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feco-village-in-los-angeles-what-life-is-like-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintentional%20community%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20we%20had%20a%20shared%20kitchen%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-roommates-and-i-share-groceries-to-save-money-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eate%20dinner%20together%3C%2Fa%3E%20six%20nights%20a%20week.%20Next%20door%20lived%20close%20family%20friends%20with%20four%20kids%2C%20and%20next%20to%20them%2C%20another%20couple%20we%20knew%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20embarrassed%20about%20it%2C%20so%20I%20hid%20it%20at%20school.%20Kids%20often%20ridicule%20anything%20different%2C%20and%20I%20just%20wanted%20to%20fit%20in.%20I%20was%20self-conscious%20that%20they'd%20call%20my%20parents%20%26quot%3Bhippies.%26quot%3B%20I%20didn't%20know%20anyone%20whose%20home%20setup%20resembled%20mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20all%20seven%20kids%20from%20across%20the%20households%20would%20be%20in%20one%20part%20of%20the%20property%20watching%20a%20movie%20or%20playing%20games%2C%20while%20the%20adults%20gathered%20elsewhere%2C%20sharing%20wine%2C%20laughter%2C%20and%20conversation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a363bbd-70b5-43db-88ea-6b2bbb4112a6%5C%22%3EI%20realized%20the%20benefits%20later%20in%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20that%20part%20of%20why%20it%20worked%20is%20because%20four%20of%20the%20adults%20were%20social%20workers.%20They%20worked%20with%20an%20interpersonal%20relationships%20expert%20who%20ran%20a%20couple%20of%20workshops%20at%20the%20start%20of%20living%20together%20about%20building%20values%20together%2C%20which%20helped%20them%20to%20divide%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteaching-my-son-to-do-chores-independently-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elabor%20of%20chores%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20maintenance%2C%20cleaning%2C%20and%20cooking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe'd%20have%20community%20days%20when%20we'd%20work%20on%20a%20group%20project%20like%20clearing%20land%20or%20digging%20a%20dam%20on%20the%20property%20%E2%80%94%20the%20parents%20within%20the%20intentional%20community%20made%20it%20fun%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20my%20late%2020s%20that%20I%20started%20reflecting%20on%20it%20as%20an%20extraordinary%20gift%20and%20a%20better%20way%20to%20live.%20I'd%20been%20so%20preoccupied%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20kids%20might%20make%20fun%20of%20living%20this%20way%20that%20I'd%20somewhat%20overlooked%20the%20many%20benefits.%20It%20offered%20a%20unique%20balance%20of%20friendship%2C%20support%2C%20and%20community%20while%20still%20providing%20the%20space%20and%20privacy%20that%20introverts%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aa682ed0-9659-4ef5-8cac-646e5dd44199%5C%22%3EWe%20decided%20to%20give%20it%20a%20shot%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20discussed%20it%20with%20my%20partner%2C%20and%20she%20was%20sold%3B%20we%20were%20curious%20about%20whether%20we'd%20be%20able%20to%20replicate%20the%20atmosphere%20in%20a%20smaller%2C%20inner-city%20dwelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202013%2C%20we've%20attempted%20it%20three%20times.%20We%20tried%20in%20Melbourne%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20despite%20initial%20interest%2C%20we%20couldn't%20get%20our%20friends%20to%20commit.%20We%20tried%20in%20Oakland%2C%20California%2C%20and%20partially%20succeeded%20by%20renting%20with%20friends%2C%20but%20part%20of%20the%20idea%20was%20to%20co-own%2C%20both%20to%20save%20costs%20and%20intentionally%20build%20a%20community.%20Finally%2C%20we%20fully%20succeeded%20in%202021%2C%20when%20we%20became%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-adults-live-with-roommates-dream-buying-property-with-friends-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eco-owners%20of%20a%20brownstone%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20New%20York%20with%20three%20friends%2C%20where%20we%20still%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20three-story%20Brooklyn%20brownstone%20we%20live%20in%20has%20eight%20bedrooms%2C%20six%20bathrooms%2C%20and%20three%20living%20spaces.%20Five%20people%20live%20here%20permanently%20(and%20generally%2C%20at%20least%20one%20or%20two%20friends%20are%20staying%20at%20any%20given%20time)%2C%20three%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-weird-habits-return-to-office-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20from%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20other%20two%20work%20a%20hybrid%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20weekly%20'family'%20dinners%20on%20Sunday%20night%20in%20the%20shared%20kitchen%2C%20hang%20out%20on%20the%20stoop%20together%20multiple%20times%20a%20week%20(usually%20spontaneously)%2C%20and%20have%20helped%20each%20other%20through%20the%20highs%20and%20lows%20of%20health%2C%20career%2C%20love%2C%20and%20day-to-day%20life.%20I'll%20often%20play%20board%20games%20for%20four%20hours%20at%20short%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paramount%20consideration%20in%20doing%20this%20was%20quality%20of%20life%2C%20but%20the%20financial%20benefits%20are%20also%20huge.%20The%20brownstone%20was%20easier%20for%20us%20all%20to%20afford%20because%20we%20pulled%20together%20and%20saved%20on%20all%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-homeowners-housing-shortage-falling-prices-values-baby-boomers-population-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecosts%20associated%20with%20buying%20a%20property%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20set%20my%20intentional%20community%20up%20slightly%20differently%20from%20the%20one%20my%20parents%20had.%20Space%20is%20a%20premium%20in%20New%20York%2C%20unlike%20in%20rural%20Australia%2C%20so%20we%20have%20three%20distinct%20units%20with%20less%20shared%20space.%20We%20hired%20a%20lawyer%20to%20draw%20up%20a%20contract%20for%20every%20potential%20scenario%2C%20from%20romantic%20separations%20to%20death%2C%20job%20loss%2C%20and%20house%20damage.%20If%20someone%20sells%2C%20the%20other%20co-owners%20get%20first%20refusal%20to%20buy%20from%20them%3B%20right%20now%2C%20we%20collectively%20pay%20a%20single%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20helped%20us%20set%20boundaries%20for%20inviting%20people%20over%20and%20solving%20issues%20with%20each%20other.%20We're%20all%20very%20social%20creatures%20by%20nature%2C%20so%20we%20love%20having%20company%2C%20and%20there%20have%20been%20no%20major%20issues%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20been%20a%20ripple%20effect%2C%20too.%20In%202022%2C%20three%20other%20friends%20replicated%20our%20exact%20model%20a%20few%20blocks%20away%20in%20their%20own%20three-unit%20brownstone.%20They've%20joined%20our%20weekly%20Sunday%20family%20dinners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProximity%20matters%20hugely%20for%20lowering%20barriers%20to%20friend%20hangouts%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20spontaneous%20ones.%20I'll%20compromise%20on%20pretty%20views%2C%20shorter%20commutes%2C%20and%20even%20the%20perfect%20apartment%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20my%20friends.%20It%20means%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20each%20day%2C%20my%20people%20are%20there%20without%20needing%20to%20think%20about%20it.%20That%20has%20enhanced%20my%20life%20more%20than%20any%20of%20those%20other%20things%20possibly%20could.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fco-own-brownstone-friends-split-costs-evenly-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741601221000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67cb633269253ccddf98aad8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fco-own-brownstone-friends-split-costs-evenly-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nick%20Allardice%2C%20his%20partner%2C%20and%20three%20friends%20co-own%20a%20brownstone%20in%20Brooklyn.%20They%20formed%20an%20%26quot%3Bintentional%20community%26quot%3B%20and%20split%20costs%20evenly.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Gary%20Nunn)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A183%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fco-own-brownstone-friends-split-costs-evenly-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Austin%20is%20the%20new%20capital%20of%20the%20robotaxi%20wars%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Waymo%20car%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c741f2b1834fe311661ccf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221799%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Jenny%20Chang-Rodriguez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20has%20a%20new%20robotaxi%20capital.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWaymo%20and%20Tesla%20are%20going%20head-to-head%20in%20Austin%2C%20lured%20by%20Texas'%20hands-