f%20performance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20or%20maybe%20you%20didn't%20get%20along%20with%20your%20past%20manager%2C%20it%20happens.%20That%20said%2C%20don't%20flag%20the%20issue%20or%20lead%20with%20it%20%E2%80%94%20only%20bring%20it%20up%20if%20you're%20directly%20asked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20recruiter%2C%20I'd%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BIs%20there%20somebody%20I%20shouldn't%20reach%20out%20to%3F%26quot%3B%20This%20typically%20opens%20the%20conversation%20for%20someone%20to%20say%2C%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3BOh%2C%20not%20my%20last%20manager.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20would%20be%20my%20way%20of%20seeing%20how%20self-aware%20the%20candidate%20is.%20The%20higher%20you%20go%20in%20your%20career%2C%20and%20the%20more%20you%20climb%2C%20not%20everybody%20will%20like%20you%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20just%20life.%20But%20do%20you%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fself-awareness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehave%20the%20self-awareness%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20know%20that%2C%20and%20can%20you%20professionally%20articulate%20why%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20might%20say%20something%20like%2C%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3BIn%20my%20last%20role%2C%20my%20manager%20and%20I%20had%20differing%20points%20of%20view%20on%20the%20best%20path%20to%20do%20XYZ%2C%20so%20that%20person%20is%20likely%20not%20going%20to%20be%20the%20best%20person%20to%20talk%20to%2C%20but%20here%20are%20the%20three%20people%20who%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228510499c-b163-4ef9-abe0-90d8da11c372%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20you%20get%20a%20bad%20reference%2C%20be%20honest%20and%20self-aware%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20calling%20references%2C%20there%20were%20times%20when%20red%20flags%20would%20come%20up%2C%20and%20the%20employer%20wouldn't%20give%20a%20positive%20review.%20So%2C%20I'd%20ask%20several%20follow-up%20questions%20to%20get%20the%20employer's%20side%20of%20the%20story.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20hearing%20them%20out%2C%20I%20would%20go%20back%20to%20the%20candidate%20to%20hear%20their%20side%2C%20too.%20I%20believe%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreen-flags-answers-personality-traits-recruiters-look-for-job-interviews-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egood%20recruiters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20should%20do%20that.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI'd%20then%20tell%20the%20candidate%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20we%20were%20doing%20these%20references.%20Can%20you%20help%20me%20understand%20your%20point%20of%20view%20on%20what%20happened%3F%26quot%3B%20Most%20recruiters%20understand%20that%20disagreements%20happen%2C%20but%20how%20the%20candidate%20handles%20it%20is%20what%20matters.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20good%20response%20might%20be%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20past%20manager%20and%20I%2C%20our%20relationship%20ended%20badly.%20Here's%20what%20happened%2C%20here's%20how%20I%20could%20have%20done%20better%2C%20and%20here's%20what%20I%20learned.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20candidates%20were%20honest%2C%20self-aware%2C%20and%20professional%2C%20I%20often%20viewed%20them%20as%20somebody%20who%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-be-happier-at-a-job-you-dont-like-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elearning%20and%20growing%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20somebody%20I%20wanted%20to%20work%20with.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f4700a9e-820d-411f-9073-b5ef5a077e0b%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EFront%20door%20references%20should%20be%20people%20who%20deeply%20know%20your%20work%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20you%20can't%20list%20your%20latest%20manager%2C%20there%20are%20others%20you%20can%20list%2