n%20School.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20worried%20that%20people%20are%20a%20little%20too%20comfortable%20and%20complacent.%20They're%20hoping%20that%20some%20people%20will%20even%20opt%20out%2C%20because%20they%20realize%20they%20can't%20live%20up%20to%20the%20performance%20standard.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20only%20one%20problem%20with%20cracking%20down%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-low-performers-zuckerberg-linkedin-job-searching-social-media-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elow%20performers%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20It%20doesn't%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20decades%20of%20rigorous%20research%20have%20demonstrated%2C%20aggressive%20efforts%20to%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-performance-cuts-mark-zuckerberg-memo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eraise%20the%20bar%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20on%20performance%2C%20as%20Zuckerberg%20put%20it%2C%20tend%20to%20backfire%20with%20remarkable%20consistency.%20CEOs%20may%20%3Cem%3Ethink%3C%2Fem%3E%20they're%20creating%20a%20meritocracy%2C%20but%20in%20reality%20they're%20marching%20their%20companies%20straight%20into%20a%20trap%20of%20sunken%20morale%2C%20high%20turnover%2C%20depressed%20profits%2C%20and%20reduced%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20short%20run%2C%20you%20might%20be%20creating%20some%20heightened%20performance%20standards%20and%20some%20accountability%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Grant%2C%20who%20serves%20as%20the%20chief%20work-life%20expert%20at%20Glassdoor.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20long%20run%2C%20you%20may%20be%20shooting%20your%20organization%20in%20the%20foot.%26quot%3B%20The%20evidence%20on%20making%20employees%20fear%20for%20their%20jobs%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20is%20clear%3A%20%26quot%3BThey're%20very%20shortsighted%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20motivates%20workers%20to%20do%20their%20best%3F%20It's%20a%20question%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-manager-hiring-white-collar-recession-layoffs-jobs-efficiency-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emanagers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20wrestling%20with%20for%20as%20long%20as%20managers%20have%20been%20around.%20Back%20when%20America%20was%20first%20industrializing%2C%20the%20prevailing%20belief%20was%20that%20the%20best%20tool%20for%20driving%20employees%20was%20fear.%20The%20influential%20management%20theorist%20Frederick%20Taylor%20argued%20that%20workers%20were%20inherently%20lazy%20and%20in%20need%20of%20constant%20supervision.%20Swooping%20into%20factories%2C%20he%20set%20brutally%20high%20productivity%20standards%20%E2%80%94%20and%20summarily%20fired%20anyone%20who%20fell%20short.%20Everyone%20else%20had%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20buckle%20down%20and%20grind%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20unsafe%20the%20new%20standards%20might%20be%2C%20or%20how%20much%20misery%20they%20provoked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Taylorism%20swept%20the%20country%2C%20it%20made%20things%20worse%20rather%20than%20better%2C%20contributing%20to%20a%20wave%20of%20strikes%20that%20left%20factories%20idle%20for%20long%20stretches.%20By%20the%201950s%2C%20many%20companies%20were%20trying%20out%20a%20kinder%2C%20gentler%20philosophy%20of%20management.%20Instead%20of%20using%20fear%20to%20drive%20workers%2C%20they%20drew%20on%20a%20host%20of%20other%20motivating%20forces%20identified%20by%20organizational%20psychologists%3A%20a%20sense%20of%20connection%20and%20community%2C%20interesting%20and%20varied%20tasks%2C%20the%20desire%20to%20be%20useful.%20But%20in%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20as%20globalization%20began%20to%20erode%20American%20competitiveness%2C%20management%20by%20fear%20came%20roaring%20back.%20At%20General%20Electric%2C%20Jack%20Welch%20famously%20ordered%20his%20managers%20to%20rank%2020%25%20of%20their%20employees%20as%20A%20players%2C%2070%25%20as%20B%20players%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20remaining%2010%25%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20were%20fired%20for%20low%20performance%2C%20as%20C%20players.%20The%20practice%2C%20which%20came%20to%20be%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Brank%20and%20yank%2C%26quot%3B%20spread%20throughout%20corporate%20America.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20management%20philosophy%2C%20it%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20disaster.%20Take%20what%20happened%20at%20Microsoft%2C%20where%20the%20rank-and-yank%20system%20was%20known%20by%20another%20name%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstack-ranking-employees-is-a-bad-idea-2013-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estack%20ranking%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%20the%20early%202010s%2C%20the%20once%20dominant%20company%20had%20watched%20its%20market%20cap%20plunge%20by%20more%20than%2050%25.%20One%20of%20the%20primary%20culprits%3F%20Its%20Welchian%20management%20system%2C%20which%20treated%20performance%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-is-filled-with-abusive-managers-and-overworked-employees-says-tell-all-book-2012-5%3Fop%3D1%23the-myth-of-the-fabulous-stock-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20zero-sum%20game%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20you%20wanted%20to%20succeed%2C%20someone%20else%20had%20to%20fail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStaffers%20were%20rewarded%20not%20just%20for%20doing%20well%20but%20for%20making%20sure%20that%20their%20colleagues%20failed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20journalist%20Kurt%20Eichenwald%20found.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%2C%20the%20company%20was%20consumed%20by%20an%20endless%20series%20of%20internal%20knife%20fights.%20Potential%20market-busting%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20e-book%20and%20smartphone%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20were%20killed%2C%20derailed%2C%20or%20delayed%20amid%20bickering%20and%20power%20plays.%26quot%3B%20By%202013%2C%20when%20Microsoft%20finally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-just-killed-its-controversial-stack-ranking-employee-review-system-2013-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabandoned%20stack%20ranking%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20much%20of%20corporate%20America%20had%20as%20well%20%E2%80%94%20including%20GE%2C%20where%20it%20all%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20long%20history%20of%20management%20by%20fear%20has%20given%20scholars%20a%20lot%20of%20data%20to%20scrutinize.%20So%20what%20has%20all%20the%20research%20found%3F%20For%20starters%2C%20using%20terror%20to%20motivate%20your%20staff%20works%20in%20the%20short%20run%3A%20When%20their%20jobs%20are%20hanging%20in%20the%20balance%2C%20employees%20work%20harder%20and%20faster.%20But%20the%20initial%20surge%20in%20productivity%2C%20studies%20have%20shown%2C%20comes%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20%3Cem%3Equality%3C%2Fem%3E.%20As%20workers%20rush%20to%20keep%20up%2C%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpsycnet.apa.org%2Fbuy%2F2002-01632-002%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutput%20is%20inevitably%20shoddier%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20riddled%20with%20mistakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20more%2C%20work%20in%20the%20performance%20pressure%20cooker%20becomes%20less%20innovative.%20Take%20a%20study%20that%20took%20place%20in%20the%201990s%2C%20at%20a%20Fortune%20500%20tech%20company%20with%20more%20than%2030%2C000%20employees.%20After%20a%20series%20of%20layoffs%2C%20the%20remaining%20high%20performers%20became%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdash.lib.harvard.edu%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F1%2F37940231%2FDownsizing-changes-in-the-work-environment-for-creativity-Amabile-Conti-1999.pdf%3Fsequence%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20creative%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20generated%20fewer%20new%20ideas%20for%20inventions.%20Organizational%20psychologists%20call%20this%20a%20%26quot%3Bthreat-rigidity%20response%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20our%20tendency%20to%20respond%20to%20fear%20by%20clinging%20to%20the%20familiar.%20The%20anxiety%20generated%20by%20job%20insecurity%20becomes%20so%20overwhelming%2C%20studies%20suggest%2C%20that%20it%20actually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fprofile%2FSusan-Stewart-16%2Fpublication%2F227783864_Productivity_Counterproductivity_and_Creativity_The_Ups_and_Downs_of_Job_Insecurity%2Flinks%2F611d6ab51e95fe241adfccdc%2FProductivity-Counterproductivity-and-Creativity-The-Ups-and-Downs-of-Job-Insecurity.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpairs%20people's%20cognitive%20functioning%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20might%20not%20matter%20so%20much%20when%20you're%20completing%20routine%20tasks%2C%20but%20it's%20debilitating%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20problem-solving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20focus%20very%20narrowly%20on%20protecting%20their%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Grant.%20%26quot%3BThey%20stop%20taking%20risks%20and%20thinking%20creatively%20and%20innovating%2C%20which%20is%20exactly%20what%20you%20need%20them%20to%20do%20in%20a%20turbulent%20environment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20employees%20fear%20for%20their%20job%20security%20also%20causes%20them%20to%20flee%3A%20One%20study%20estimated%20that%20laying%20off%20just%201%25%20of%20a%20workforce%20would%2C%20on%20average%2C%20lead%20to%20a%2031%25%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fprofile%2FCharlie-Trevor%2Fpublication%2F211395271_Keeping_Your_Headcount_When_All_About_You_Are_Losing_Theirs_Downsizing_Voluntary_Turnover_Rates_and_The_Moderating_Role_of_HR_Practices%2Flinks%2F0f317539b2284c8a3b000000%2FKeeping-Your-Headcount-When-All-About-You-Are-Losing-Theirs-Downsizing-Voluntary-Turnover-Rates-and-The-Moderating-Role-of-HR-Practices.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espike%20in%20voluntary%20turnover%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20might%20not%20sound%20so%20terrible%20for%20a%20company%20that's%20trimming%20its%20head%20count%2C%20but%20the%20departures%20aren't%20random.%20High%20performers%2C%20who%20have%20the%20most%20options%2C%20leave%20in%20far%20larger%20numbers%20than%20mediocre%20employees.%20Creating%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-today-tech-jobs-anxiety-zirp-careers-layoffs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eculture%20of%20fear%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20makes%20it%20harder%20to%20recruit%20high%20performers.%20In%20one%20study%2C%20businesses%20that%20conducted%20layoffs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fciteseerx.ist.psu.edu%2Fdocument%3Frepid%3Drep1%26type%3Dpdf%26doi%3D68ccbb559e86ea445c83696a4e8279e4ae02958e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eslid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Fortune's%20rankings%20of%20the%20most%20admired%20companies.%20The%20more%20you%20slash%20your%20low%20performers%2C%20the%20fewer%20high%20performers%20you'll%20wind%20up%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPretty%20much%20every%20study%20that%20has%20ever%20crunched%20the%20numbers%20has%20found%20the%20same%20thing%3A%20Contrary%20to%20what%20leaders%20like%20Zuckerberg%20and%20Musk%20believe%2C%20instilling%20fear%20in%20employees%20actually%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fd1wqtxts1xzle7.cloudfront.net%2F46417505%2FDumb_and_Dumber_The_Impact_of_Downsizing20160612-5886-grp8rc-libre.pdf%3F1465741604%3D%26response-content-disposition%3Dinline%253B%2Bfilename%253DDumb_and_Dumber_The_Impact_of_Downsizing.pdf%26Expires%3D1740604425%26Signature%3DWXbFqoaRQijGqglKLyrNkUvpW9JIWi2v3nKRiNCuZe8GmMvc6qMmF5nG~Mi6L2Xw4j4gqo3XKCMbFe3T8jfGuYpAd8MfAyrjXqdN9~O2ccUCZJdesyl0yngrX3OqBy-lgxTrltznFAijpLNeq0p~6fbZKYntJPjxUqkR5S2Z4H6x3uTgRqEFBAoWdKJHFfS4USgSqOQ-WH4z6XkhvGkugjZm~JL3TiIuSOJXeJAAVL9~5vGkmn7UJNuG~8oZUd-nhz8DOxt2MVRdaD~p7jO-bRtvx5oktgE-aI1p7dVJfU9atyGS24ZH4oSj7JRWka27lbmjWX620reN-JaNp64crA__%26Key-Pair-Id%3DAPKAJLOHF5GGSLRBV4ZA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehurts%20a%20company's%20profitability%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20That%20effect%20is%20particularly%20large%20in%20R%26amp%3BD-intensive%2C%20high-growth%20industries%20like%20tech.%20The%20feelings%20of%20uncertainty%20that%20job%20cuts%20engender%20end%20up%20paralyzing%20businesses%20instead%20of%20turbocharging%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20destructive%20practice%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sandra%20Sucher%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20who%20studies%20layoffs.%20%26quot%3BIf%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20thinks%20that%20this%20is%20inspiring%20to%20people%20to%20do%20a%20better%20job%2C%20he%20needs%20a%20primer%20on%20how%20it%20is%20that%20people%20are%20motivated.%20Most%20people%20aren't%20sufficiently%20motivated%20by%20fear%20to%20actually%20do%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20to%20say%20that%20CEOs%20should%20run%20their%20companies%20like%20Montessori%20preschools.%20There%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20things%20that%20Taylor%20got%20right%20a%20century%20ago%3A%20setting%20high%20standards%2C%20monitoring%20employee%20output%2C%20rewarding%20people%20who%20do%20well.%20Those%20remain%20the%20cornerstones%20of%20good%20management%20today.%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20some%20companies%20may%20have%20swung%20a%20little%20too%20far%20to%20the%20gentle%20side%2C%20suspending%20performance%20reviews%20altogether.%20It%20was%20an%20expression%20of%20empathy%20that%20recognized%20the%20extraordinary%20stresses%20of%20the%20crisis%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20left%20some%20managers%20with%20no%20idea%20what%20their%20employees%20were%20doing%2C%20let%20alone%20how%20well%20they%20were%20doing%20it.%20High%20performers%20weren't%20getting%20recognized%20and%20rewarded%2C%20and%20low%20performers%20weren't%20getting%20the%20help%20they%20needed.%20Many%20bosses%20blamed%20the%20chaos%20on%20remote%20work%2C%20and%20ordered%20everyone%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eback%20to%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20the%20real%20problem%20was%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20properly%20functioning%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-performance-evaluations-management-reviews-promotions-raises%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esystem%20of%20performance%20management%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20big%20difference%20between%20being%20demanding%20and%20being%20demeaning%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Grant.%20%26quot%3BDemanding%20is%20about%20saying%3A%20'Look%2C%20we%20have%20extremely%20high%20expectations.%20We%20hired%20you%20because%20we%20believe%20you're%20capable%20of%20meeting%20them.%20Here%20are%20your%20goals.%20Let's%20talk%20through%20what%20I%20can%20do%20to%20help%20you%20achieve%20them.'%20Then%2C%20if%20somebody%20is%20not%20pulling%20their%20weight%2C%20you%20give%20them%20feedback%20%E2%80%94%20you%20let%20them%20know%20what%20they%20need%20to%20change.%20If%20they're%20not%20willing%20or%20able%20to%20change%20it%2C%20yes%2C%20of%20course%2C%20at%20some%20point%20you%20let%20them%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20demeaning%20way%3F%20It's%20basically%20the%20approach%20being%20taken%20by%20Zuckerberg%20and%20Musk.%20Setting%20arbitrary%20quotas%20of%20the%20number%20of%20employees%20who%20should%20get%20cut.%20Forcing%20managers%20to%20fire%20people%20who%20were%20consistently%20told%20they%20were%20meeting%20and%20exceeding%20expectations.%20Publicly%20labeling%20them%20as%20%26quot%3Blow%20performers%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20hurts%20their%20chances%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffind-job-searching-hunt-tips-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elanding%20a%20new%20job%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20above%20all%2C%20failing%20to%20recognize%20that%20an%20employee%20who%20isn't%20working%20out%20isn't%20just%20a%20failure%20of%20the%20individual.%20It's%20also%20a%20failure%20of%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%26quot%3B%20Grant%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20seems%20to%20be%20in%20vogue%20right%20now%20is%20a%20more%20demeaning%20approach%20to%20leadership.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20overwhelming%20evidence%20against%20management%20by%20fear%2C%20it's%20puzzling%20why%20Silicon%20Valley%20is%20trying%20to%20revive%20it.%20The%20tech%20industry%2C%20after%20all%2C%20was%20founded%20on%20the%20belief%20that%20everything%20should%20be%20dictated%20by%20data.%20Grant%20blames%20ignorance.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20talk%20with%20CEOs%2C%20many%20of%20them%20are%20just%20unaware%20of%20the%20evidence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey%20haven't%20thought%20through%20the%20unintended%20consequences%20of%20their%20decisions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESurely%2C%20though%2C%20it%20shouldn't%20be%20difficult%20for%20a%20company%20like%20Microsoft%20to%20remember%20just%20how%20poorly%20things%20went%20the%20last%20time%20it%20went%20after%20low%20performers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20much%20better%20it%20did%20once%20it%20replaced%20stack%20ranking%20with%20Satya%20Nadella's%20softer%20approach%20of%20%26quot%3Bmodel%2C%20coach%2C%20care.%26quot%3B%20Microsoft%20post-2013%20is%20one%20of%20the%20great%20success%20stories%20of%20the%20past%20decade%20%E2%80%94%20an%20ailing%20giant%20that%20actually%20managed%20to%20become%20relevant%20again.%20The%20tech%20industry%20boomed%2C%20in%20no%20small%20part%2C%20because%20starry-eyed%20startups%20motivated%20their%20coders%20and%20product%20managers%20and%20salespeople%20with%20the%20promise%20that%20they%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhustle-culture-got-america-addicted-to-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echanging%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Eager%20millennials%20were%20happy%20to%20devote%20their%20nights%20and%20weekends%20to%20make%20that%20mission%20a%20reality%2C%20and%20they%20turned%20their%20underdog%20employers%20into%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20businesses%20in%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hugely%20frustrating%2C%20because%20we%20become%20smart%20for%20a%20while%20and%20then%20we%20become%20stupid%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sucher%2C%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20professor.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20you've%20been%20in%20business%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20which%20I%20have%20now%2C%20you%20get%20used%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20goes%20in%20cycles%20like%