the%20world%20in%20his%20joint%20address%20to%20the%20US%20Congress%20last%20week.%20The%20ramifications%20of%20the%20over%2090-minute%20speech%2C%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20longest%20delivered%20in%20decades%2C%20would%20be%20experienced%20in%20America%20in%20the%20weeks%20ahead%20as%20DOGE%20Chief%20Elon%20Musk's%20slashes%20have%20begun%20to%20stir%20the%20cauldron.%20%C2%A0It%20is%20here%20that%20the%20politics%20inside%20the%20Beltway%2C%20as%20Washington%20politics%20is%20identified%2C%20would%20determine%20the%20course.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20two%20distinct%20and%20discernible%20threads%20in%20the%20February%2025%20speech%2C%20which%2C%20in%20essence%2C%20was%20a%20reiteration%20and%20elaboration%20on%20the%20issues%20he%20flagged%20during%20the%20campaign.%20One%2C%20Trump%20outlined%20how%20his%20administration%20was%20rolling%20out%20plans%20to%20take%20America%20on%20the%20path%20to%20regaining%20its%20%E2%80%9Cgreatness%E2%80%9D%20and%20ushering%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgolden%20era%E2%80%9D.%20The%20other%20was%20a%20distinct%20display%20of%20partisanship%20that%20is%20now%20a%20more%20pronounced%20feature%20of%20American%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmericans%20Have%20Never%20Been%20More%20Divided%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAware%20of%20the%20sharp%20polarisation%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20Democratic%20leadership%20had%20suggested%20its%20members%20not%20to%20react%20to%20Trump%20in%20a%20fashion%20that%20would%20give%20Republicans%20a%20chance%20to%20shape%20the%20narrative.%20But%20that%20proved%20difficult%20as%20handheld%20signs%20and%20placards%20populated%20the%20area%2C%20conveying%20objection%20to%20several%20measures%20that%20the%20new%20administration%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeep%20divisions%20were%20on%20full%20display.%20While%20some%20Democrats%20carried%20placards%20reading%20%E2%80%9CSave%20Medicaid%E2%80%9D%2C%20others%20flashed%20cards%20that%20had%20%E2%80%9CLies%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9CProtect%20Veterans%E2%80%9D%20written%20on%20them%20as%20Trump%20read%20out%20a%20long%20list%20of%20budgetary%20allocations%20made%20under%20the%20previous%20administration%20allegedly%20for%20%E2%80%98dubious'%20or%20%E2%80%98non-priority'%20beneficiaries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimultaneously%2C%20senior%20Democratic%20Congressman%20Al%20Green%20of%20Texas%20was%20escorted%20out%20of%20the%20House%20for%20interrupting%20the%20President's%20speech.%20It%20was%20Green%20who%20had%20moved%20an%20impeachment%20motion%20against%20President%20Trump%20in%20his%20first%20term%3B%20in%20fact%2C%20last%20month%2C%20he%20had%20threatened%20to%20do%20so%20again.%20Many%20women%20members%20turned%20up%20in%20pink%20attire%20to%20protest%20policies%20they%20said%20were%20against%20women%2C%20while%20a%20few%20staged%20a%20walkout.%20Towards%20the%20end%2C%20most%20Democrats%20swiftly%20exited%20the%20floor%20while%20Republicans%20stood%20applauding%20the%20address.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETaking%20Everyone%20Along%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20weeks%20ahead%2C%20Trump%20and%20his%20team%20will%20require%20the%20support%20of%20Congress%20to%20pass%20proposals%20and%20to%20usher%20in%20tax%20reforms%20and%20policies.%20This%20will%20require%20amending%20existing%20laws.%20The%20Republicans%20control%20both%20the%20House%20and%20the%20Senate%2C%20though%20with%20a%20slender%20majority.%20Typical%20political%20play%20on%20The%20Hill%20will%20require%20dexterous%20deal-making.%20That%20is%20the%20challenge%20the%20administration%20of%20the%20day%20faces%2C%20despite%20its%20inherent%20strength.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20experience%20during%20the%20first%20term%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20acutely%20aware%20of%20how%20Members%20of%20Congress%2C%20even%20those%20belonging%20to%20the%20Republican%20Party%2C%20can%20throw%20a%20spanner%20in%20his%20plans.%20Unlike%20in%20parliamentary%20democracy%2C%20where%20a%20whip%20forces%20members%20to%20toe%20the%20party%20line%2C%20on%20the%20Hill%2C%20each%20bill%20requires%20negotiation.%20It%20is%20not%20unusual%20for%20members%20of%20one%20party%20to%20support%20a%20Bill%20floated%20by%20a%20member%20from%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20aisle.%20These%20voting%20patterns%20are%20dictated%20by%20the%20policies%20and%20commitment%20of%20members%20on%20issues%20they%20or%20their%20constituents%20advocate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Will%20GOP%20Act%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20mentioning%20his%20plan%20to%20offer%20tax%20breaks%20for%20interest%20on%20loans%20taken%20for%20cars%20made%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20President%20Trump%20pointed%20towards%20the%20Democrats%20and%20encouraged%20them%20to%20pass%20it%20along%20with%20a%20few%20other%20measures%20thrown%20in%2C%20like%20ending%20taxes%20on%20tips%2C%20overtime%20pay%2C%20and%20social%20security%20benefits.%20In%20his%20typical%20style%2C%20President%20Trump%20mocked%20the%20Democrats%3A%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20And%20I%20am%20sure%20people%20on%20my%20right%20%E2%80%93%20I%20don't%20mean%20the%20Republican%20right%20but%20my%20right%20here%20%5Boccupied%20by%20Democrats%5D%20%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20I%20am%20sure%20you%20are%20going%20to%20vote%20for%20those%20tax%20cuts%20because%20I%20don't%20believe%20people%20will%20ever%20vote%20for%20you%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20doing%20you%20a%20big%20favour%20by%20telling%20you%20that.%E2%80%9D%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20President%20Trump's%20comment%20riled%20the%20Democrats%2C%20the%20administration%20has%20to%20factor%20in%20how%20the%20GOP%20acts.%20Days%20ahead%20of%20the%20speech%2C%20the%20House%20voted%20narrowly%E2%80%94217%20to%20215%E2%80%94to%20take%20forward%20the%20Republican%20plan%20for%20President%20Trump's%20legislative%20agenda.%20This%20was%20after%20an%20all-day%20effort%20managed%20to%20convince%20a%20few%20Republicans%20to%20come%20on%20board%20at%20the%20last%20minute.%20The%20priorities%20included%20measures%20for%20border%2C%20energy%2C%20and%20taxes%20and%20was%20the%20first%20major%20test%20for%20the%20Grand%20Old%20Party%20(GOP)%20and%20Speaker%20Mike%20Johnson%2C%20who%20had%20to%20cancel%20round%20one%20of%20voting%20and%20then%20call%20it%20again.%20There%20was%20a%20group%20of%20Republican%20conservatives%20who%20were%20not%20convinced%20to%20support%20the%20measure%20as%20it%20did%20not%20reduce%20the%20deficit%20enough.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20shows%20there%20is%20no%20easy%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20section%20of%20GOP%20lawmakers%20baulked%20over%20Trump's%20suggestion%20to%20the%20Speaker%20to%20%E2%80%9Cget%20rid%E2%80%9D%20of%20CHIPS%20and%20Science%20Act.%20The%202022%20Act%20provided%20%2452%20billion%20for%20domestic%20semiconductor%20manufacturing%20and%20had%20strong%20bipartisan%20support.%20Add%20to%20this%20the%20general%20sense%20of%20discomfort%20the%20Democratic%20lawmakers%20are%20experiencing.%20They%20would%20be%20out%20to%20stall%20the%20President's%20agenda%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20new%20administration%20seeks%20to%20amend%20laws%20passed%20during%20Biden's%20tenure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20chasm%20between%20the%20lawmakers%20on%20either%20side%20reflects%20the%20gulf%20in%20American%20politics%20that%20emerged%20during%20Trump's%20first%20term%2C%20continued%20during%20the%20interim%20period%2C%20and%20has%20resurfaced%20with%20much%20more%20force%20now.%20It%20makes%20the%20task%20difficult%20for%20moderates%20in%20either%20party%20to%20agree%20on%20a%20midpoint.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(K.V.%20Prasad%20is%20a%20senior%20Delhi-based%20journalist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741588260000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fod7s9lk8_donald-trump-reuters_625x300_07_March_25.jp